article.headline: GoHealth to offer 39.5 million shares in planned IPO, priced at $18 to $20 each
article.body: GoHealth Inc., a health insurance marketplace, set terms for its planned initial public offering on Wednesday, with plan to offer 39.5 million shares priced at $18 to $20 each. The company would raise $790 million at the top of that range. The company has applied to list on Nasdaq under the ticker with plans to list on Nasdaq under the ticker symbol "GOCO." There are 11 banks underwriting the deal, led by Goldman Sachs.
